MK-1500
Nay 21, 1962
Mr. W. K. Bu Chief Engineer Shilmmen Development Commission Shihifen Comp
Subject: OSA Surplus Equipment
Dear Mr. Kus
GSA Catalog Number 408-GP-I & III indicates the following items available which we recommend be procured through the regular channels.
Page 21, GSA Control No. 4-62-10379, 1-1026-62-207, Commodity Group No. 11, 4140-506-1799, Fan Axivane, motor blower assembly 1960, electric AC 200V, 3 ph, Joy lifg. Co. Model AVF 42-35D794, P/H x 702-109%, A. G. $209,00 da, TAC $418.00, Condition Code Quantity and Unit Auto, Release Date H-1, 2 es, 6-10.
Page 22, GSA Control No. 4-62-10865, HSTG-8-226-62, Commodity Group No. 43, 4320, Pump immersion, 3 stage, sz 28, XXL.VIB, 5500GPM, 840 RPM, 245 hd. Bryon Jackson, Co. Complete w/ con- troller magnetic clutch, 600 HIP induction elect. mtr. Mfr. Louis- Allis Co. 660-1741620. A. C. $15,000.00 Condition Code Quantity and Unit Auto. Release Date 1-2, 1 os, 6-19.
The above listed pump would be excellent to have on hand during the final closure operations of the diversion tunnel.
It is our understanding that the equipment is available at no cost to the Project.
Attached catalogue should be returned to Mr. Carter after your use.
Very truly yours,
MORRISON_KNUDSEN OF ASIA, INC.
İlen & Johnson Glenn C. Johnson Project Manager
Enel. C.C. Dam Construction Dept. Mr. J. B. Carter
